laboratory_examinations.findings: Normal sinus rhythm at 84 beats per minute with sinus arrhythmia and diffuse T-wave flattening
Extensive thrombus with a lack of venous compressibility and absent respiratory variability, indicating obstructing DVTs
Complete agenesis of the IVC with an extensive system of serpiginous venous collaterals providing drainage from the abdomen
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Invasive venography showed thrombotic occlusion of the right common femoral vein and left femoral vein

laboratory_examinations.findings: Patent right-sided femoral and common femoral veins with improved patency in the left common femoral and iliac veins
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Reduction in thrombus burden with improvement in venous collateralization after catheter-directed thrombolysis
